<p><strong>Rome (CNN)</strong> -- The Roman Catholic Church will declare the late Pope John Paul II a saint, the Vatican announced Friday.</p>
<p class="cnn_storypgraphtxt cnn_storypgraph2">Pope Francis signed the decree Friday morning, the Vatican said. John Paul was pope from 1978 until his death in 2005, and was in a way the first rock star pontiff, drawing vast crowds as he crisscrossed the globe.</p>
<p class="cnn_storypgraphtxt cnn_storypgraph3">At his funeral, thousands of pilgrims gathered in St. Peter's Square and chanted "Santo subito" -- Sainthood now! The Polish-born pope was fast-tracked to beatification and became "the blessed" John Paul II barely six years after his death, the fastest beatification in centuries.</p>
